                    <span>The book is useful to get started on nio, but you may overgrow it after a week:<BR>it does not delve deeply into the matter. Particularly missing are:<BR>- Mapped byte buffer uses<BR>- Interactions between java & else using mapped files<BR>- OS/platform idiosyncrasies (limits etc)<BR>- Performance analysis<P>Finally, be aware that half of the book is devoted to regular expressions. The conflagration of nio and regexps is rather strange. I would rather have a shorter book with just a little more depth.</span>
                  
              
